  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bonbatu +</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Three months of Cash-for-Work (April-June) consisting of land rehabilitation work activities, followed by two months of unconditional Cash Grants (July-August).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2018;Bonbatu&#x2019; speaks of resilience in Zarma, meaning &#x2018;I protect myself&#x2019; or &#x2018;I become stronger,&#x2019; which is precisely what this project aims to help vulnerable households achieve. CRS Niger has worked in the Tillab&#xE9;ri and Ouallam departments for years providing emergency assistance, including two projects responding to immediate food needs during the 2011-2012 food crisis. 

Following the successful implementation of Project Bonbatu (2012-2014), CRS Niger is continuing its emergency food aid and development activities in Ouallam department through &quot;Bonbatu +&quot;. The project will help 830 vulnerable households in five villages through Cash-for-Work and Cash Grants during the 2014 lean season.</narrative>
  </description>
